Pre-Game Insights: A win for Pakistan keeps them in contention for a semi-final, victory for South Africa ensures their final-four spot
Experts highlighted the high-quality pace bowling attacks from both teams
Pakistan's attack has been labeled the best in the tournament by their own legspinner Shadab Khan
Pakistan have had the better of South Africa in T20s recently, winning both the home and away series against them in 2021
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played on the same pitch as the Sri Lanka-New Zealand game, where Trent Boult took a career-best 4 for 13
Sydney is the only venue at the tournament where teams have breached 200
Pakistan have a 3-0 win record against South Africa at the T20 World Cup, even though they last met in 2012
Others: South Africa's batting line-up is unlikely to change as long as they're winning
Fakhar Zaman has been ruled out of the match with a knee injury
The average first innings score in Sydney at this tournament so far is 188, the highest of the venues used
